<subSubSection id="8AD3A2879E45FD0AB2B63D116AE92FED" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="A87AC6DC87E635AA9EDBADB41100CAF5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8AD54330A89713F910254B600F2805E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">This species is rather variable in leaf size and shape, indumentum and corolla size. Entire leaves are deltoid and basally truncate, but the deeply 3-lobed leaves have the terminal leaflet somewhat rhomboid in form. The indumentum is quite variable in its density and the branched hairs are not easily discerned even with a microscope.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
